  "text": "The Kafka producer record flow traces from ProducerRecord through RecordAccumulator to the Sender thread and finally through NetworkClient to network transmission:\n\n1. **ProducerRecord (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/ProducerRecord.java)**: User-facing class representing a key/value record to be sent to Kafka with topic, partition, key, value, and headers.\n\n2. **KafkaProducer.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/KafkaProducer.java:1029)**: Entry point for sending records. Serializes the record and calls RecordAccumulator.append() to accumulate the record into batches.\n\n3. **RecordAccumulator.append() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java:275)**: Accumulates records into ProducerBatch instances, organizing them by topic partition. Manages memory buffer allocation and creates new batches as needed.\n\n4. **RecordAccumulator.ready() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java:763)**: Batch ready check that determines which nodes have batches ready to send by evaluating linger time, batch fullness, and partition availability.\n\n5. **Sender.run() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java:236)**: Main sender thread loop that repeatedly calls runOnce() which invokes sendProducerData().\n\n6. **Sender.sendProducerData() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java:357)**: Calls accumulator.ready() to identify ready nodes, then calls accumulator.drain() to extract batches for sending.\n\n7. **RecordAccumulator.drain() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java:954)**: Drains batches from the accumulator for nodes that are ready to send, removing them from the queue and returning them organized by node ID.\n\n8. **Sender.sendProduceRequests() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java:856)**: Iterates through drained batches and calls sendProduceRequest() for each node.\n\n9. **Sender.sendProduceRequest() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java:864)**: Constructs a ProduceRequest from the batches, creates a ClientRequest, and calls client.send() to send the request.\n\n10. **NetworkClient.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/NetworkClient.java:541)**: Delegates to doSend() to handle protocol versioning and request serialization.\n\n11. **NetworkClient.doSend() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/NetworkClient.java:601)**: Serializes the request, creates an InFlightRequest, and calls selector.send() to queue the serialized data for network transmission.\n\n12. **Selector.send() (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/network/Selector.java:391)**: Places the NetworkSend into a KafkaChannel queue, which will be transmitted over the socket during the next poll() cycle."
}

